      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yup, OK. But we’re not so concerned with the final form of MemorySnapshotIOS, the one that reads things out of the serialized format, right? Right now, we’re working with these temporary snapshot implementations that are actually poking around in the live process.\n\nEven in this case, the buffer_ member is unnecessary. You can defer reading the memory until Read.\n\nAs I discussed, in reality, when this graduates to vm_read, you’ll want to do so in PAGE_SIZE-chunks, with a PAGE_SIZE-sized stack buffer.",
