      "message": "At least in this CL, this is called in thread_snapshot_ios with:\n stack_.Initialize(stack_region_address, stack_region_size);\n\nIf we don\u0027t copy over the data, stack_region_address and size are meaningless pointers.\n\nThe final form of MemorySnapshotIOS will be very different, but right now we are doing \u0027both sides\u0027 of data collection in-process.  We are making sure we can get all the data we need, and making sure we can massage it into the format we need to dump things into snapshot.  This is kind of bridging the gap?\n\nI\u0027m fine taking an alternate approach, but that\u0027s where my thoughts are here.  WDYT?",
